==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Spearmint
<hw>Spear"mint`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[So named from its
<ets>spiry</ets>, not capitate, inflorescence. <au>Dr.
Prior.</au>]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A species of mint (<spn>Mentha
viridis</spn>) growing in moist soil. It vields an aromatic oil. See
<er>Mint</er>, and <er>Mentha</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Spearwood</ent>⟦br⟧
